Cyclic ES module graphs (A imports B, B imports A) hit `#!~debt
esm-cyclic-live-bindings` in the blob-URL trampoline.  The browser's
import() needs the dep blob URLs baked into each module's source, but
blob URLs are immutable — we can't pre-mint a URL for a record whose
source isn't generated yet (and the source needs the cyclic dep's
URL).  Real fix paths:
  (a) install a service-worker that serves source from our registry at
      stable per-record URLs (e.g. blob-fake:edge/<id>) — preserves
      V8's bytecode-level live-binding semantics
  (b) rewrite all imports through a JS-runtime namespace registry —
      simpler but lossy for re-export-from-cycle patterns

For now the registry throws a clear "edge.js ESM cycle detected" error
instead of stack-overflowing.  Tracked in NOTES.md as
esm-cyclic-live-bindings.  Static (non-cyclic), TLA, dynamic, and
re-export tests cover the rest of the surface.
